## Responsive design and CSS tokens

- Design tokens are defined in [src/styles/tokens.css](mdc:src/styles/tokens.css). Use CSS variables (e.g., `var(--brand-primary)`).
- Base utilities and resets live in [src/styles/base.css](mdc:src/styles/base.css). Components in [src/styles/components.css](mdc:src/styles/components.css). Layout in [src/styles/layout.css](mdc:src/styles/layout.css).
- Grids: use `.grid-3` and `.grid-2`; they collapse to 1 column at `max-width:980px`.
- Containers: wrap sections with `.container` and spacing from `section{ padding: ... }`.
- Responsiveness: media queries defined in `layout.css` adjust nav, grids, hero, and spacing at `980px`.
- RTL/LTR handled by `<html dir>` set in JS; keep CSS logical properties where feasible.